System Overview:
The Personal Practice Tracker is a web application that helps people build consistent practice habits for skill-based activities by giving them a structured way to log sessions, set goals, and view progress trends over time. The system is built to make effort feel measurable again when progress becomes slow or hard to notice, so users can stay consistent without needing formal coaching or external accountability. 
The primary users are individuals practicing independently, including students, musicians, athletes, and hobbyists. The main workflows include account creation and login, creating one or more practice skills or routines, logging practice sessions with notes and optional performance metrics, viewing dashboards that summarize streaks and trends, generating date-range reports, and optionally receiving reminders or suggested practice focus areas based on past patterns.

