The React frontend is responsible for the user interface, including forms for logging sessions, dashboards, and data visualization. The Flask backend exposes a REST API that handles authentication, validation, business rules (streaks, summaries, analytics), and all database interactions. PostgreSQL stores persistent data for users, skills/goals, and practice logs. External services are optional and are called from the backend when enabled, so secrets are not exposed in the client. Data flows from the UI to the API via JSON requests, the API validates and processes the request, persists it to the database, and returns summary data for rendering and charting.

